&gt; Take a look at the TestSetup class.  This is a TestDecorator that adds
&gt; setup
&gt; and teardown arround a group of test
&gt; 
&gt; From the 3.5 FAQ
&gt; 
&gt; How do I run setup code once for all my TestCases?
&gt; Wrap the top level suite in a subclass of TestSetup. Here is a sample
&gt; AllTests.suite() method:
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; public static Test suite() {
&gt;   TestSuite suite= new TestSuite();
&gt;   ...add your tests and suites here...
&gt;   TestSetup wrapper= new TestSetup(suite) {
&gt;    public void setUp() {
&gt;     oneTimeSetUp();
&gt;    }
&gt;   };
&gt;   return wrapper;
&gt; }
&gt; 
&gt; I hope this helps
